children.text: The Termguard perimeter termite system pipes have been installed with pipe runs greater than 16m (lineal metres), which is not in accordance with the manufacturer’s technical installation manual.
The Termguard technical installation manual states that
‘The maximum distance the 20mm drilled pipe can protect is 16mts in the external perimeter from the manifold connection’ .

As the building surveyor has determined that this dwelling is in a designated termite zone, the builder will need to ensure that this termite system is properly installed to prevent infestation in accordance with the manufacturer’s technical installation manual.
